;; M-typed-memories P0 fixture suite — 14 hand-written memory_record payloads
;; Written 2026-07-22 (DERIVE, examples-first discipline: shape must express
;; these naturally BEFORE any code; invariant I-M5 = first-try acceptance of
;; all 14). Sources: TN-zai2-session-notes-2026-07-22 Part 2 (M1-M8, math,
;; from zai-1's a94J06 session zai-b14ff8a657ec476dbe375a0339d5da3a) and
;; Part 3 (O1-O6, ops, from zai-2's session zai-188835e2ae3d433195f20b3ec9c8d882).
;;
;; PAYLOAD CONTRACT (P0, act fixed = :assert; agent sends this, server stamps
;; :evidence/author :evidence/session-id :evidence/at and auto-links the
;; current turn-round — see Finding F3):
;;   :name         kebab slug (identity hint; server may suffix for uniqueness)
;;   :hook         one line, ≤80 chars — THE projection/index column (Stage 1)
;;   :kind         :feedback | :reference | :project | :user  (see Finding F2)
;;   :body         the fact, prose; self-contained
;;   :why          because-clause (encouraged for :feedback; optional)
;;   :how-to-apply retrieval predicate / application condition (optional)
;;   :subjects     REQUIRED, ≥1 ArtifactRef {:ref/type kw :ref/id str};
;;                 FIRST = primary (entry subject), rest = extra endpoints
;;                 (see Finding F1; requiredness settled at review 2026-07-22:
;;                 EvidenceEntry demands a subject, so the schema says so
;;                 up front rather than erroring after acceptance)
;;   :distills     optional vector of evidence ids the memory distills;
;;                 "@current-round" = server resolves to the in-flight
;;                 turn-round (agents don't know their own evidence ids —
;;                 Finding F3); placeholders marked for ingest-test resolution
;;   :facets       vector of facet path strings (P0: stored in props;
;;                 promoted to facet entities at P3)
;;   :volatile?    optional; true = valid-until-changed (Finding F4; P2's
;;                 natural retract candidates)
;;
;; ============================================================
;; MATH (a94J06, Putnam 1994 A6 — zai-1)
;; ============================================================

[{:name "mul-inv-rev-for-inverse-products"
  :hook "(a*b)⁻¹ needs mul_inv_rev; mul_comm only reorders separate inverses"
  :kind :feedback
  :body "To rewrite (ζ-z)⁻¹ * ζ⁻¹ into (ζ*(ζ-z))⁻¹ use mul_inv_rev. mul_comm merely swaps the factors, giving ζ⁻¹ * (ζ-z)⁻¹, which is not the inverse-of-product shape the goal wants."
  :why "mul_comm proved the wrong equality — the goal needed the inverse of a product, not a reordered product of inverses; caught as a ✘ self-correction."
  :how-to-apply "When a Lean goal equates a product of inverses with an inverse of a product, reach for mul_inv_rev (and mul_inv/inv_inv variants) before commutativity lemmas."
  :subjects [{:ref/type :library :ref/id "Mathlib"}
             {:ref/type :problem :ref/id "apm/a94J06"}]
  :distills ["@current-round"]
  :facets ["math/lean/mathlib-api" "math/complex-analysis"]}

 {:name "no-rw-under-circle-integral-notation"
  :hook "rw cannot pattern-match inside ∮ notation — convert/simp or restate in ⁻¹ form"
  :kind :feedback
  :body "rw with circleIntegral.integral_congr fails to pattern-match integrands inside the circle-integral binder. Working alternatives: simp only [one_div] to normalize first, convert instead of rw, or — the durable fix — state all integrands in ⁻¹ form throughout the development so lemma forms match syntactically."
  :why "Adopted mid-proof as an architectural convention after repeated rw failures; the 1/x vs x⁻¹ mismatch was the recurring cause."
  :how-to-apply "When rewriting under ∮/circleIntegral (or any binder-heavy notation), do not rw; normalize the statement's integrand form at declaration time."
  :subjects [{:ref/type :library :ref/id "Mathlib"}
             {:ref/type :problem :ref/id "apm/a94J06"}]
  :distills ["@current-round"]
  :facets ["math/lean/tactics" "math/complex-analysis/contour-integration"]}

 {:name "integral-congr-needs-everywhere-equality"
  :hook "integral_congr wants equality at EVERY point — thread the excluding hypothesis"
  :kind :feedback
  :body "circleIntegral.integral_congr requires pointwise equality on the whole circle, not a.e. When the integrand identity fails at exactly one point (ζ = z), do not abandon the strategy: carry the hypothesis that keeps the bad point off the circle (‖z‖ ≠ 1) into the helper lemma."
  :why "The first partial-fractions attempt failed at the single point ζ = z, was abandoned for direct evaluation (which dead-ended), then re-adopted successfully once ‖z‖ ≠ 1 was threaded — the failure was never the algebra. (The A → B → A′ route of a94J06.)"
  :how-to-apply "Before abandoning an integrand-rewrite strategy over a pointwise failure, check whether an available hypothesis excludes the failing point; thread the hypothesis instead of switching strategies."
  :subjects [{:ref/type :library :ref/id "Mathlib"}
             {:ref/type :problem :ref/id "apm/a94J06"}]
  :distills ["@current-round"]
  :facets ["math/lean/tactics" "math/complex-analysis/contour-integration" "math/proof-strategy"]}

 {:name "field-simp-can-close-goals-via-sorry"
  :hook "field_simp may 'close' a goal by inserting sorry — recount after"
  :kind :feedback
  :body "field_simp can report a goal closed while having introduced a sorry (observed once in a94J06: goal gone, sorry count up). A tactic 'success' is not proof progress until the sorry count and clean build confirm it."
  :why "Trust calibration: the tactic's apparent success masked a hole; only the grep -c sorry check exposed it."
  :how-to-apply "After any field_simp that closes a goal unexpectedly easily, re-run the sorry count and a clean compile before moving on."
  :subjects [{:ref/type :library :ref/id "Mathlib"}
             {:ref/type :problem :ref/id "apm/a94J06"}]
  :distills ["@current-round"]
  :facets ["math/lean/tactics"]}

 {:name "ring-does-not-handle-inv"
  :hook "ring fails on goals containing ⁻¹ — clear inverses first or ring_nf"
  :kind :reference
  :body "The ring tactic does not know inv: goals containing ⁻¹ fail. Clear inverses first (field_simp with the needed ≠ 0 hypotheses) or use ring_nf."
  :how-to-apply "Seeing ring fail on a field identity: check for ⁻¹ in the goal before doubting the identity."
  :subjects [{:ref/type :library :ref/id "Mathlib"}]
  :distills ["@current-round"]
  :facets ["math/lean/tactics"]}

 {:name "zpow-form-not-defeq-product-form"
  :hook "ζ^(-2) ≠defeq (ζ*ζ)⁻¹ — rfl fails across zpow/product forms; ring_nf"
  :kind :reference
  :body "ζ^(-2) is not definitionally equal to (ζ*(ζ-0))⁻¹ even after sub_zero: zpow unfolds to (ζ^2)⁻¹ and ζ^2 is not syntactically ζ*ζ. rfl fails; ring_nf normalizes both sides."
  :how-to-apply "When rfl fails between algebraically-equal zpow and product-of-inverses forms, use ring_nf before hunting for a bridging lemma."
  :subjects [{:ref/type :library :ref/id "Mathlib"}]
  :distills ["@current-round"]
  :facets ["math/lean/tactics" "math/lean/defeq"]}

 {:name "rw-direction-for-equality-hypotheses"
  :hook "h : a = b — rw [h] sends a→b; rw [← h] sends b→a; check goal side first"
  :kind :reference
  :body "With h : a = b, rw [h] rewrites occurrences of a into b; rw [← h] rewrites b into a. Before writing the rw, identify which side actually occurs in the goal."
  :why "This confusion recurred three times in one session (a94J06) — a first-occurrence memory would have paid for itself twice before the proof closed."
  :how-to-apply "Any rw with an equality hypothesis: name the side present in the goal, then choose the arrow."
  :subjects [{:ref/type :library :ref/id "Lean4"}]
  :distills ["@current-round"]
  :facets ["math/lean/tactics"]}

 {:name "negate-le-with-not-le-of-gt"
  :hook "contradicting ≤ (closedBall gives ≤) needs not_le_of_gt, not not_lt_of_gt"
  :kind :reference
  :body "mem_closedBall_zero_iff yields ‖w‖ ≤ 1. To contradict it with 1 < ‖w‖ use not_le_of_gt; not_lt_of_gt negates a strict <, which is not what closedBall membership gives."
  :how-to-apply "Match the negation lemma to the relation in the hypothesis being contradicted: ≤ pairs with not_le_of_gt, < with not_lt_of_gt (ball strict, closedBall non-strict)."
  :subjects [{:ref/type :library :ref/id "Mathlib"}]
  :distills ["@current-round"]
  :facets ["math/lean/mathlib-api"]}

