 {:name "clj-file-underscore-ns-hyphen"
  :hook "file zai_api.clj ↔ ns zai-api — reflect takes ns form, file tools take path form"
  :kind :reference
  :body "Clojure munging: namespace futon3c.agents.zai-api lives in file agents/zai_api.clj. reflect_ns and friends take the namespace spelling (hyphens); read_file/search take the path spelling (underscores). 'Namespace not found: futon3c.agents.zai_api' means a filename-shaped string was passed as a namespace."
  :how-to-apply "Translate _ ↔ - at the tool boundary: hyphens for reflection tools, underscores for file tools."
  :subjects [{:ref/type :language :ref/id "clojure"}
             {:ref/type :tool :ref/id "reflect_ns"}]
  :distills ["@current-round"]
  :facets ["ops/clojure" "ops/zai-tools"]}

 {:name "search-tool-is-java-regex-escape-braces"
  :hook "search compiles Java regex — literal { } must be escaped or 'Illegal repetition'"
  :kind :reference
  :body "The zai search tool compiles its pattern as a Java regex. Literal braces — e.g. searching Clojure/EDN source for {:name — parse as repetition quantifiers and fail with 'Illegal repetition'. Escape them (\\{) or drop them from the pattern."
  :how-to-apply "Searching for EDN/Clojure map literals: escape { } (and other regex metacharacters) in the search pattern."
  :subjects [{:ref/type :tool :ref/id "search"}]
  :distills ["@current-round"]
  :facets ["ops/zai-tools"]}

 {:name "run-readonly-heuristic-false-positives"
  :hook "run_readonly rejects innocuous compound commands — fall back to run_shell"
  :kind :feedback
  :body "run_readonly's destructive-command heuristic rejects some genuinely read-only compound commands (redirects/heredocs pattern-match as destructive). The fallback is run_shell. Hit zai-1 and zai-2 independently on the same day (2026-07-22)."
  :why "First concrete cross-agent case in the corpus: an environment memory either agent could have contributed and both would consume."
  :how-to-apply "For read-only compound shell with redirection, go straight to run_shell; keep run_readonly for simple single-purpose reads."
  :subjects [{:ref/type :tool :ref/id "run_readonly"}]
  :distills ["@current-round"]
  :facets ["ops/zai-tools"]}

 {:name "futon1b-http-on-7073-not-7074"
  :hook "futon1b store HTTP = 127.0.0.1:7073; :7074 (backend default) not listening"
  :kind :reference
  :volatile? true
  :body "The futon1b store JVM serves HTTP/EDN on 127.0.0.1:7073. Port 7074 — the default-url in futon3c's futon1b_backend.clj — is not listening. An evidence query against the wrong port returns empty/unreachable while the data exists (zai-2: 0 entries via :7074, 100 via the in-process store). Empty result ≠ no data; check the path first."
  :why "Diagnosed retrospectively in-session: 'the earlier query failed because I was querying via the wrong path.'"
  :how-to-apply "Before concluding 'no evidence', verify the topology (ss -tlnp | grep 707, or query in-process via drawbridge)."
  :subjects [{:ref/type :service :ref/id "futon1b"}]
  :distills ["@current-round"]
  :facets ["ops/futon1b/topology"]}

 {:name "zai-quota-two-token-windows"
  :hook "z.ai quota: two TOKENS_LIMIT windows; unit-6 binds the 50% cron gate"
  :kind :reference
  :volatile? true
  :body "The z.ai quota API reports two TOKENS_LIMIT windows. The unit-6/number-1 window is the one apm_formal_zai_cron's MIN_AVAILABLE_PERCENT=50 gate binds on; the unit-3/number-5 window can show 95% available while dispatch is still gated."
  :how-to-apply "Reading the quota for dispatch decisions: check the unit-6 window, not the healthiest-looking one."
  :subjects [{:ref/type :service :ref/id "z.ai-quota"}
             {:ref/type :script :ref/id "futon3c/scripts/apm_formal_zai_cron.py"}]
  :distills ["@current-round"]
  :facets ["ops/zai-quota"]}

 {:name "restored-agents-not-invoke-ready"
  :hook "Agency :restored ≠ dispatchable — flip to :idle via drawbridge before belling"
  :kind :feedback
  :body "Agents in :restored status on the Agency roster are not selectable for dispatch (not :idle, no invoke-ready). Flip the registry entry to :idle via drawbridge eval so invoke-ready? true / invoke-route local holds, then bell."
  :why "The a94J06 dispatch stalled on this until zai-1 was flipped; the failure mode is silent (bell accepted, nothing runs)."
  :how-to-apply "Pre-dispatch checklist: roster status must be :idle (invoke-ready), not :restored; check GET /api/alpha/agents before any bell to an agent you have not belled recently."
  :subjects [{:ref/type :service :ref/id "futon3c-agency"}]
  :distills ["@current-round"]
  :facets ["ops/agency"]}]

