;; ============================================================
;; SHAPE FINDINGS forced by writing these 14 (DERIVE q4 output):
;;
;; F1 SUBJECT MULTIPLICITY. EvidenceEntry has ONE :evidence/subject; half
;;    the fixtures naturally want two (library + problem, tool + language).
;;    Resolution: payload :subjects is a vector; first = primary (entry
;;    subject), all become hyperedge endpoints. No schema change needed —
;;    multiplicity lives where it belongs (the edge).
;;
;; F2 KIND BOUNDARY RULE. feedback-vs-reference was fuzzy for tactic facts
;;    until this rule settled every case: derived-from-a-failure-with-a-why
;;    → :feedback; documented contract/scope fact → :reference. The rule
;;    belongs in the tool description. (M4/M5 are the boundary pair: same
;;    domain, different kinds, both natural under the rule.)
;;
;; F3 AGENTS CANNOT KNOW EVIDENCE IDS. :distills wants the turn-round id,
;;    but the agent never sees its own persist-round! ids — demanding them
;;    would recreate the psr/pur "Invalid evidence shape" failure class.
;;    Resolution: "@current-round" sentinel resolved server-side; explicit
;;    ids allowed when the agent has them (from memory_search results).
;;
;; F4 VALIDITY HORIZON WANTS A HINT. Both volatile fixtures (O4, O5) begged
;;    for a marker distinguishing valid-until-changed from ~timeless.
;;    :volatile? true is the minimal P0 hint; P2 turns it into real
;;    valid-time handling (volatile memories are the natural first retract
;;    candidates — O4 will be superseded by the very hardening/wiring work
;;    in flight).
;;
;; F5 (negative finding) NOTHING NEEDED :act IN THE PAYLOAD. All 14 are
;;    natural asserts; P0's act-fixed design is confirmed. The A→B→A′
;;    story fit inside M3's :why without needing retract edges — the
;;    retract belongs to P2, when the *next* session contradicts a memory,
;;    not to the initial recording.
;; ============================================================
